en_213691_0	The notice was issued on the CEB today ordering it to appear before the Colombo Magistrate Court on April 9 for its failure to provide reports with regard to the current power cuts to the Public Utility Commission.
en_213691_1	Public Utility Commission had wanted such reports since the month of May 2018 but the CEB has not provided them so far.
en_213691_2	CEB chairman and 8 of his deputies have been named as respondent of this case filed by the Public Utility Commission.
en_213691_3	Accordingly, Colombo Fort Magistrate Ranga Dissanayake issued notice on the CEB ordering it to appear before him on April 9.
